The paper deals with the graph isomorphism problem, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses semidefinite programming, which is a mathematical optimization technique commonly used in computational geometry (cs.CG) and combinatorial optimization (cs.DM). The paper also involves the study of graph structures and their properties, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG).
